
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gpg-zip` baraye zakhire-kardan (archive) va ramez-negari (encrypt) file-ha ba estefade az GnuPG (GPG) be kar miravad. In dastoor file-ha ra compress mikonad va ba kelid-e shakhsi shoma ramez-negari mikonad, ta amniat-e aanha ra ta’min konad. 🔒

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gpg-zip file.txt` --> 📝 File `file.txt` ra compress va ramez-negari mikonad.
    🔹 `gpg-zip -r recipient file.txt` --> 👤 File `file.txt` ra baraye `recipient` ramez-negari mikonad (recipient bayad ID ya email address bashad).
    🔹 `gpg-zip -o output.gpg file.txt` --> 📤 File `file.txt` ra compress va ramez-negari mikonad va dar file `output.gpg` zakhire mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gpg-zip myfile.txt

    🔹 File `myfile.txt` compress va ba kelid-e pish-farz ramez-negari mishavad.

    $ gpg-zip -r "User Name <user@example.com>" myfile.txt

    🔹 File `myfile.txt` baraye shakhsi ba email `user@example.com` ramez-negari mishavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gpg-zip -o archive.gpg important_document.txt

    🔹 File `important_document.txt` compress va ba estefade az GPG ramez-negari mishavad, natije dar file `archive.gpg` zakhire mishavad. 💾

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gpg-zip` command is used to archive and encrypt files using GnuPG (GPG). It compresses files and encrypts them with your personal key, ensuring their security. 🔒

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gpg-zip file.txt` --> 📝 Compresses and encrypts the file `file.txt`.
    🔹 `gpg-zip -r recipient file.txt` --> 👤 Encrypts `file.txt` for the specified `recipient` (recipient must be an ID or email address).
    🔹 `gpg-zip -o output.gpg file.txt` --> 📤 Compresses and encrypts `file.txt` and saves it to `output.gpg`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gpg-zip myfile.txt

    🔹 Compresses `myfile.txt` and encrypts it using the default key.

    $ gpg-zip -r "User Name <user@example.com>" myfile.txt

    🔹 Encrypts `myfile.txt` for the person with the email `user@example.com`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gpg-zip -o archive.gpg important_document.txt

    🔹 Compresses and encrypts `important_document.txt` using GPG, saving the result in `archive.gpg`. 💾
